%% Diagram: End-to-end encryption flow (PrivateBin / 0bin model)
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant W as Writer browser
    participant API as Paste service
    participant S3 as Object storage
    participant R as Reader browser

    Note over W: WebCrypto generates<br/>random 256-bit AES-GCM key
    W->>W: zlib compress
    W->>W: AES-256-GCM encrypt(content, key, iv)
    W->>API: POST /pastes {ciphertext, iv, kdf_params}
    API->>S3: PUT pastes/{paste_id}.bin (ciphertext)
    API-->>W: 201 {paste_id}
    W->>W: build URL: https://host/{paste_id}#key=<base58>
    Note over W,API: Server only sees ciphertext.<br/>Fragment after # is never sent.

    R->>API: GET /{paste_id}<br/>(fragment stays in browser)
    API->>S3: GET pastes/{paste_id}.bin
    S3-->>API: ciphertext
    API-->>R: 200 {ciphertext, iv, kdf_params}
    R->>R: read key from window.location.hash
    R->>R: AES-256-GCM decrypt + zlib decompress
    R->>R: render plaintext + highlight client-side
